<h1>WHAT I DO (CURRENT SETUP):</h1>  <p>Currently, we use SVN as our SCM and Maven-Mule-REST-Plugin (<a href="https://github.com/NicholasAStuart/Maven-Mule-REST-Plugin" rel="nofollow">link</a>) to deploy the apps to MMC. Below is how we do the development / check-in / build / deploy (using a custom JAR tool).</p>  <p>(1) Upload to SVN after developing and unit-testing with pom.xml (2) Make a note of the SVN revision number (after commit) (3) Put that in a XML file (which is what the tool refers - see below XML_ScreenShot1). (4) When the tool (java code in a jar file) is triggered,  => the XML_ScreenShot1 is referred and the project (artifactId) is checked-out in the workspace => copy the mmc.xxx / svn.rev.number / artifactId variables from above XML and put in the app's pom.xml (see below XML_ScreenShot2) => trigger mvn build/deploy using the plugin</p>  <p>NOTE: By this way we are maintaining each build (in MMC) with svn_rev number and its a internal IT dept decision.</p>  <h1>WHAT I WANT:</h1>  <p>Trying to use Jenkins-CI, with existing process as SVN-Checkin , add the custom pom's value and call the maven plugin.</p>  <h1>WHERE AM I WITH Jenkins:</h1>  <p>I am successful in getting the Jenkins up and running, making builds by checkout and pushing with mvn plugin.</p>  <h1>WHAT I AM MISSING:</h1>  <p>I am able to publish the mule.zip after maven build to MMC using its REST API.</p>  <p>But for this I hardcoded the RootPom in Jenkins-Job configuration to the 'SVN Project name / pom.xml' (Refer log file line 104). How can I refer the checked-out directory (which I see is the same name as the project name in SVN) as an environment variable. Please see the attached config and log files; kindly help me in resolving the issue.</p>  <p>What I have now: ROOTPOM = hello-world-dev-jenkins/pom.xml</p>  <p>What I am looking is something like this: ROOTPOM = %SVN_CURRENT_CHKOUT_DIR%/pom.xml</p>  <p>And also I have to add the custom Values to the pom.xml before maven kicks in, where I am having challenges.</p>  <pre><code>XML_ScreenShot1 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ &lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;project xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;     &lt;properties&gt;         &lt;muleEnv&gt;dev&lt;/muleEnv&gt;         &lt;pomLocation&gt;C:/SVN-MMC-CDA/properties/&lt;/pomLocation&gt;         &lt;svnWorkSpaceLocation&gt;C:/CDA/svnWorkSpace/dev/&lt;/svnWorkSpaceLocation&gt;         &lt;svn.url&gt;http://subverserver01/svn/CAD/Mule/&lt;/svn.url&gt;         &lt;svn.username&gt;svnmmcCDA&lt;/svn.username&gt;         &lt;svn.password&gt;svnmmcCDA&lt;/svn.password&gt;         &lt;mmc.muleApiUrl&gt;https://mmcdev01:18443/mmc/api/&lt;/mmc.muleApiUrl&gt;         &lt;mmc.username&gt;mmcDevRESTAPIUser&lt;/mmc.username&gt;         &lt;mmc.password&gt;mmcDevRESTAPIPasswd&lt;/mmc.password&gt;         &lt;mmc.serverGroup&gt;mmcMuleDev&lt;/mmc.serverGroup&gt;     &lt;/properties&gt;     &lt;deployments&gt;         &lt;deployment&gt;             &lt;action&gt;DEPLOY&lt;/action&gt;             &lt;repoLocation&gt;branches&lt;/repoLocation&gt;             &lt;artifactId&gt;hello-world-app-jenkins&lt;/artifactId&gt;             &lt;svn.rev.number&gt;1571&lt;/svn.rev.number&gt;         &lt;/deployment&gt;     &lt;/deployments&gt; &lt;/project&gt; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ </code></pre>  <p>After copying the custom values, the app's pom.xml will look like below.</p>  <pre><code>XML_ScreenShot2 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ &lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?&gt; &lt;project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/maven-v4_0_0.xsd"&gt;     &lt;modelVersion&gt;4.0.0&lt;/modelVersion&gt;     &lt;artifactId&gt;hello-world-app-jenkins&lt;/artifactId&gt;      &lt;properties&gt;         &lt;muleEnv&gt;dev&lt;/muleEnv&gt;     